article.headline: Yale 79, Cornell 63
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Sam Kaplan made seven of nine field goals and scored 16 points, one short of his career high, as Yale beat Cornell 79-63 Friday night. Dominick Martin added 15 points and 12 rebounds for the Bulldogs, who snapped a three-game losing streak and evened their record at 6-6 in Ivy play. The Bulldogs (10-15) opened the game with a 16-4 run, capped by a jumper by Edwin Draughan with 14:10 left. The lead grew to 20, 30-10, on a Martin layup with 8:14 remaining. Yale (12-14, 7-6 Ivy) led 42-27 at halftime and opened the second half with 9-3 run. Draughan added 14 points and Casey Hughes scored 11 for the Bulldogs. Eric Taylor had 14 points to lead Cornell, while Lenny Collins scored 10 points and grabbed seven rebounds.
